Key Match Events: The Sacramento Kings defeated the Boston Celtics 114-97 on January 11, 2025.
The game was tied at 76 entering the fourth quarter.
Devin Carter led an 8-2 run at the start of the fourth quarter.
Domantas Sabonis finished with 23 points and 28 rebounds.
Keegan Murray scored 19 points, including 5-of-8 from three-point range.
DeMar DeRozan had 24 points and 9 assists.
Malik Monk contributed 22 points and 8 assists.
Post-Match Reflections: Doug Christie and Keon Ellis agreed to let Devin Carter stay in the game due to his performance.
Keegan Murray praised Doug Christie for instilling confidence in the players.
The Kings have now won 6 straight games and are back to .500 for the season.
